modules.description: This module provides functions to initialize, query, and close a geolocation database, retrieving country information (codes, names) and geographic IDs from IPv4/IPv6 addresses, IP numbers, or hostnames. It operates on a structured database handle and related types, supporting use cases like regional content delivery, location analytics, and network security tools that require geolocation metadata. Additional capabilities include database metadata inspection (edition, character set) and geographic ID lookups for advanced geospatial workflows.
